Interface AMAuditService

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.forgerock.audit.AuditService, org.forgerock.json.resource.RequestHandler
    All Known Implementing Classes:

    public interface AMAuditService
extends org.forgerock.audit.AuditService
    Extended interface of the commons AuditService to allow for OpenAM specific configuration.

      • isAuditEnabled

        boolean isAuditEnabled(String topic,
                       AuditConstants.EventName eventName)
        Determines if the audit service is auditing the specified topic and eventName. If you do not know the eventName (i.e. any event names is valid) you may pass in null.
        Parameters:
        topic - The auditing topic.
        eventName - The auditing event name, may be null for all event names
        Returns:
        true if Auditing is switched on and if the topic and eventName should be audited.
